      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BILLABONG ROSE (1) hasn't threatened in her last two when tackling much tougher opposition but gets a sharp drop in grade now. Was a barnstorming winner at Dubbo in a BM58 three back. If she can recapture that form she's the one to beat. ST ROY (8) showed good early dash and stalked the pace last start before drawing clear to score at Gilgandra. Not much tougher this time and is likely to be in the finish again. ULTRA WHITE (10) has been much better in her last two without breaking through. Backs up quickly and gets in light with the claim. Don't underestimate. ADVISER (9) was in the money two starts back at Orange but couldn't back it up last time. Well placed back at this level and is right in the mix. THE GIT UP (5) showed good early speed and raced on the pace last start before fading at Cowra. Not as tough this time and can figure.",
